wiki.content:
"Domino" is a song by English singer-songwriter Jessie J from her debut studio album, Who You Are (2011). The song was released on 29 August 2011 as the fifth single from the album. It was written by Jessie J, Dr. Luke, Claude Kelly, Max Martin and Cirkut, and it was produced by Dr. Luke and Cirkut. The song became Jessie J's second number-one single in the UK, following the Dr. Luke-produced "Price Tag" (2011). In the United States, the song peaked at number 6 on the Billboard Hot 100, becoming her most successful single.
 The song was produced by Dr. Luke and Cirkut and premiered via the singer's official YouTube channel on Tuesday, 26 September. Jessie also launched a competition to accompany the track's debut, inviting fans to post their own covers of "Domino" for a chance to win tickets to a concert in either New York or London as well as a private meet and greet session. Jessie J said the song was inspired Whitney Houston's classic "I Wanna Dance With Somebody" (1987), as she wanted to write "something uptempo, fun, everyone can sing along to it, every age can dance to it."
 "Domino" serves as Jessie's second single in the United States, after the release of "Price Tag". It was also released as the fourth single in Australia and New Zealand, being released digitally on 29 August 2011. The single was released both digitally and physically on 4 November in Germany. The single will be sixth release by Jessie in the UK and will be released on 27 February 2012.
